# Beyond# (Beyond Statistics Initiative) Landing Page Implementation Plan

Create a premium, full-screen hero landing page for **Beyond# (Beyond Statistics Initiative)** using a split-panel layout, autoplaying video background, Google Fonts, and a custom liquid glass morphism design.

## User Review Required

We need to confirm the following decisions. Please review and provide feedback.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Tailwind CSS Version**
> We will default to configuring **Tailwind CSS v3** or **Tailwind CSS v4**. We propose using Tailwind CSS v4 as it is modern and works natively with Vite plugins, but if your local workflow requires v3, we can configure v3 instead. Please specify in your approval.
> 
> **React Template**
> We will default to the standard **React with JavaScript** template (`react`) to match the "Javascript for logic" core guidelines. If you prefer TypeScript, please let us know.

## Open Questions

1. **Tailwind CSS Version**: Do you prefer Tailwind CSS v3 or v4? (We recommend v4 for its streamlined build and modern capabilities).
2. **Beyond# Logo Image**: The design requests a Beyond# logo image (`/logo.png`). We will create a premium SVG logo placeholder in public/logo.png (or generate one) until a final logo asset is provided. Does that work?
3. **Thumbnail Image for Community Impact Lab**: We will use a generated premium visual asset or high-quality SVG placeholder representing data intelligence for the Community Impact Lab thumbnail. Do you have a preferred image file?

---

## Proposed Changes

We will initialize a clean Vite + React app directly inside `C:\Users\rilwan.usman.NRS\.gemini\antigravity\scratch` and install Tailwind CSS, Lucide React, and support for Google Fonts.

### Project Setup & Configuration

#### [NEW] [package.json](file:///C:/Users/rilwan.usman.NRS/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/package.json)
Contains project metadata, scripts, and dependencies:
- `react`, `react-dom`
- `lucide-react`
- `tailwindcss` (with `@tailwindcss/vite` if v4, or standard postcss config if v3)

#### [NEW] [vite.config.js](file:///C:/Users/rilwan.usman.NRS/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/vite.config.js)
Vite configuration file. If using Tailwind v4, we will use `@tailwindcss/vite` plugin.

#### [NEW] [index.html](file:///C:/Users/rilwan.usman.NRS/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/index.html)
Includes the Google Fonts imports:
- Poppins (weights 300, 400, 500, 600, 700)
- Source Serif 4 (italic, weight 400/500)

---

### Core Styles

#### [NEW] [src/index.css](file:///C:/Users/rilwan.usman.NRS/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/src/index.css)
Defines CSS variables, imports Tailwind, and implements custom `.liquid-glass` and `.liquid-glass-strong` classes under the `@utility` or `@layer components` directive.

We will define the liquid glass morphic borders using `::before` pseudo-elements with gradients and absolute positioning, avoiding standard border classes as requested.

```css
@layer components {
  .liquid-glass {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.01);
    background-blend-mode: luminosity;
    backdrop-filter: blur(4px);
    box-shadow: inset 0 1px 1px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .liquid-glass::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    border-radius: inherit;
    padding: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15) 0%, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02) 100%);
    -webkit-mask: linear-gradient(#fff 0 0) content-box, linear-gradient(#fff 0 0);
    -webkit-mask-composite: xor;
    mask-composite: exclude;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .liquid-glass-strong {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
    backdrop-filter: blur(50px);
    box-shadow: 
      4px 4px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05),
      inset 0 1px 1px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .liquid-glass-strong::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    border-radius: inherit;
    padding: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3) 0%, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05) 100%);
    -webkit-mask: linear-gradient(#fff 0 0) content-box, linear-gradient(#fff 0 0);
    -webkit-mask-composite: xor;
    mask-composite: exclude;
    pointer-events: none;
  }
}
```

---

### Layout and Components

#### [NEW] [src/App.jsx](file:///C:/Users/rilwan.usman.NRS/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/src/App.jsx)
Main entry component holding the layouts:
- **Cinematic Video Background**: HTML5 video covering viewport (`object-cover w-full h-full absolute inset-0 z-0`), playing the provided URL in a loop, muted and autoplaying.
- **Content Overlay**: Positioned at `relative z-10`, split into two main panels:
  - **Left Panel (55% width, `w-[55%] min-h-screen`)**: Contains navigation, vertically-centered hero title with serif emphasis, mission text, primary CTA with micro-animations, strategic tags, and the bottom quote.
  - **Right Panel (45% width, `w-[45%] lg:flex flex-col min-h-screen`)**: Utility bar, floating Insight card, bottom features area containing side-by-side monitor/policy cards, and a bottom image card with an interactive action button.

---

## Verification Plan

We will verify the implementation through local build testing, browser inspection, and visual audit.

### Automated Tests
- Run `npm run build` to ensure there are no compilation or bundle errors.

### Manual Verification
- Test autoplay, looping, and muting of the background video.
- Verify fonts load and render correctly (Poppins for headings and body; Source Serif 4 italic style on targeted text).
- Check responsiveness: Left panel covers 100% on small screens, right panel displays side-by-side (`lg:flex`) on larger viewports.
- Confirm liquid glass styling, glow borders, and hover micro-animations interact smoothly.

